  <title>Floating point Literals</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Currency</keyword>
    <keyword>Currency Literal</keyword>
    <keyword>Floating point Literals</keyword>
    <keyword>Literals</keyword>
    <keyword>Numeric Literals</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Floating point Literals</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Single or double precision literals may be used to store numeric values in your code.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; color:#000000;">123.456</text><br/><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; color:#000000;">123.0</text><br/><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; color:#000000;">0.123</text><br/><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; color:#000000;">.123</text><br/><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; color:#000000;">123.456e+7</text><br/><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; color:#000000;">123.456e-7</text><br/><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; color:#000000;">$123.45</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Real literals may have one of the following suffixes:</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="4" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Suffix</para>
        </td>
        <td>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">S or s</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Single precision (REAL4)</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">D or d</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Double precision (REAL8)</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">M or m</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Decimal</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Floating point literals without suffix are stored as REAL8, unless you have specified the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="opt-vo14">/vo14</link> compiler option, in which case they are stored as FLOAT literals.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">Prefix</para>
        </td>
        <td>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal">$</para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="CURRENCY">Currency</link> Literal</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
